title: [FINAL PROPOSAL] 12/11 Governance Changes: Prelim Quorum, Voting Period
body:
Doodle ID for Kudos: #9399

**Discourse**: https://forum.doodles.app/t/adjusting-prelim-quorum-and-snapshot-voting-duration/1341

**Vote**: 
* Reduce Preliminary Vote Quorum from 15% to 10%, and
* Increase Voting Period from 2 days to 3 days.
* Implement no changes

**Rationale**:
* With the constant moving of hands and attention in the NFT Space, the Doodlebank has shown growing pains of not reaching quorum for both highly and lowly discussed proposals.
* Reducing preliminary vote quorum from 15% to 10% and increasing the duration of a vote from 2 days to 3 days will help remedy current growing pains as we adapt and develop the system further.

**Moving forward**: 
* Guidelines/rules for proposals directly addressing the system will be developed.
* Awareness and use of the system will continue to be worked on.
* Snapshot Saturdays will be internally started with expectations of proposal writers to be in active communication with myself to best organize their releases.

**Timeline**: Ongoing until further changes.

**Goal**: To alleviate current growing pains of the Doodlebank and allow more thinkers to create value in their ideas and push them forward.

**Cost**: 0 ETH

**Accountability**: As the Project Manager (Community), it is my role to better our current system around the Doodlebank and adjust to what the team and I believe is necessary. Final proposals still require approval from the team to prevent any abuse of the system.

**Vote Info**:
- Quorum (Undeveloped, Systematic Proposals): 15%
- Options: Yes to both changes or No to both changes.
